-- Pioneer says to sell DJ equipment business to KKR for $550 mln
-- By Junko Fujita
-- Tue Sep 16, 2014 02:14AM EDT
-- None



TOKYO, Sept 16 (Reuters) - Japanese car electronics maker Pioneer Corp <6773.T> said on Tuesday that it would sell its disc-jockey equipment business to private equity firm KKR & Co LP <KKR.N> for about 59 billion yen($550 million).

Pioneer has been selling off non-core assets to focus on its automotive electronics business. On Friday, the company said it would sell its home audio-visual business to audio equipment maker Onkyo Corp <6628.T>. [ID:nT9N0QS02N]